Erin Bates (SABC Digital News) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories CAPE TOWN &ndash; On Friday morning NDPP Shaun Abrahams appeared before the justice committee to answer for his conduct.He fielded questions on his decision to withdraw charges against Minister of Finance Pravin Gordhan.&nbsp;Scroll down the text to watch the proceedings.Abrahams answered to the justice committee as to his conduct charging three former Sars officials including the Finance Minister, before backtracking on that case.The NPA brought charges against Gordhan and two co-accused Ivan Pillay and Oupa Magashula over Pillay's early retirement from Sars.However, after announcing those charges in early October saying taking the NPA for granted were over.Later that month he did an unapologetic turnaround on the charges of fraud and corruption against the three."Am I embarrassed or disappointed? I don't really want to answer that question. I certainly don't want to answer that question," he said.Abrahams said during the same conference, "I certainly don't think this matter was a blunder. As lawyers we differ on interpretation, application of the law."MPs including a former NPA prosecutor who is facing charges of fraud, Glynis Breytenbach, grilled Abrahams on his conduct."Do you have any grasp of the consequences of your actions?" asked Breytenbach."Do you have any conception of the kind of stress, discomfort and personal agonising you put Mr Pillay, Mr Magashula, and Mr Gordhan through?"Watch the live stream courtesy of SABC Digital News on YouTube.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.